03/09/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ruling Justice and Development Party is in favour of declaring adultery a crime, Justice Minister Cemil Cicek said Thursday (2 September), adding that the party wants a clause to this effect included in the draft of the Turkish Penal Code, which is to be discussed in parliament later this month.
Concerning religious marriages and polygamy, Cicek said the penal code should not allow second marriages.
He insisted that the draft is in accordance with EU principles and regulations.
(NTV - 02/09/04)
